Female: Brachypterous, length 4.4–5.9. COLORATION: As in male. SURFACE AND VESTITURE: Similar to male, but body often with shallow punctation, entire dorsum and abdomen clothed with flattened silver setae, pale brown simple setae somewhat shorter than in male, erect, as long as width of hind tibia on head, pronotum, and bases of hemelytra, semiadpressed and shorter elsewhere. STRUCTURE AND MEA- SUREMENTS: Body 2.4–3.2× as long as width of pronotum. Head: 1.3–1.4× as wide as high, vertex 2.6– 3.4× as wide as eye; antennal segment II 0.7–0.9× as long as basal width of pronotum, 0.8–1.0× as long as width of head. Thorax: Pronotum 2.0–2.5× as wide as long and 1.0–1.2× as wide as head; length of hemelytra ranging from reaching middle of abdominal tergum IV to reaching abdominal tergum IX, typically reaching basal margin of tergum VII, clavus not delimited, claval suture as long as or somewhat shorter than inner margin of clavus, posterior margin of hemelytra truncate, lateral margin rounded. GENITALIA: Dorsal labiate plate as wide as long, with somewhat dentate medial sclerites and broad pigmented area between rings (fig. 16); sclerotized rings oval; posterior wall of bursa copulatrix with uniformly sclerotized trapeziform sclerite, with thin incision on the anterior margin not reaching middle of sclerite, anterior angles of this sclerite not dentate, posterior margin without sclerites (fig. 18); vulva with straight sclerites not forming a circle (as in fig. 19,
